## Fix missing User-Agent header on 3 raw-requests call sites

### Context
Audit of all outbound HTTP call sites revealed 3 `requests.get` calls that built their own `headers` dict and omitted `User-Agent: ontobricks`:
- `PermissionService._get_user_groups` — SCIM v2 user lookup
- `PermissionService._check_admin_rest` — Databricks App permissions REST check
- `SettingsService` permissions diagnostic — `_req.get` for app permissions

All other call sites (41 `requests`/`Session` calls, all `httpx` calls) already carry the header via `HTTP_USER_AGENT`, `DatabricksAuth.get_auth_headers()`, or client-level headers.

Note: Databricks SDK paths (`api_client.do`, high-level SDK) use the SDK's own User-Agent — those are not modified.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/registry/PermissionService.py` — added `HTTP_USER_AGENT` import; added `"User-Agent": HTTP_USER_AGENT` to headers in `_get_user_groups` (SCIM call) and `_check_admin_rest` (permissions call).
2. `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py` — added `HTTP_USER_AGENT` import; added `"User-Agent": HTTP_USER_AGENT` to headers in the permissions diagnostic REST call.

### Modified files
- `src/back/objects/registry/PermissionService.py`
- `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`

### Test result
87 passed — zero failures.

