## Declare user authorization scopes in app.yaml.template

### Context
The Databricks Apps auth docs (Public Preview) require explicit OAuth scope declaration
for user authorization even when using the platform defaults. OntoBricks uses
`x-forwarded-access-token` exclusively for permission checks (SCIM + App ACL read);
all data queries go through the service principal M2M token. Adding the scope declaration
makes the authorization model explicit and compliant with marketplace requirements.

### Changes
1. `app.yaml.template` — added `authorization.user.scopes` block with
   `iam.current-user:read` and `iam.access-control:read` (minimum scopes for permission
   checks; also the platform defaults, now made explicit).
2. `app.yaml` — re-rendered from template (`scripts/_render-app-yaml.py`).

### Modified files
- `app.yaml.template`
- `app.yaml`

### Test result
Static config change only. Re-render completed without errors.

