## Scripts consistency fixes

### Context
Audit of all scripts in `scripts/` revealed several inconsistencies: `setup.sh` was missing the `--extra pitfalls` flag used by `start.sh`; `Makefile bootstrap-lakebase` was missing the `-b` branch argument present in `deploy.sh`; `Makefile bundle-validate` was missing `--var=app_name` and `--var=mcp_app_name`; the `install` target used the deprecated `uv pip install -e .` instead of `uv sync`; and `start.sh`/`stop.sh` used `#!/bin/bash` while all other scripts use the portable `#!/usr/bin/env bash`.

### Changes
1. `scripts/setup.sh` — changed shebang to `#!/usr/bin/env bash`; upgraded `set -e` to `set -euo pipefail`; added `--extra pitfalls` to `uv sync` call so setup installs the same extras as `start.sh`.
2. `scripts/start.sh` — changed shebang to `#!/usr/bin/env bash`.
3. `scripts/stop.sh` — changed shebang to `#!/usr/bin/env bash`.
4. `Makefile` — `install` target: replaced `uv pip install -e .` with `uv sync --extra lakebase --extra pitfalls`; `bootstrap-lakebase` target: added missing `-b "$$LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_BRANCH"` flag; `bundle-validate` target: added missing `--var=app_name` and `--var=mcp_app_name`.

### Modified files
- `scripts/setup.sh`
- `scripts/start.sh`
- `scripts/stop.sh`
- `Makefile`

### Test result
Tests hang on network-dependent async calls to Lakebase (pre-existing, unrelated to these changes). Script-only changes — no Python code modified.
